title: Grateful Dead Live at Frost Amphitheatre on 1989-05-07
description: Iko Iko, Little Red Rooster, Bertha, Me & My Uncle-> Mexicali Blues, Built To Last, Picasso Moon, Bird Song Foolish Heart, Victim Or The Crime, Crazy Fingers, Women Are Smarter-> He's Gone-> Drums-> Jam-> The Other One-> Black Peter-> Turn On Your Love Light, E: Knockin' On Heaven's Door

reviews.review_text:
INTENSE other 1 The other 1 from this night is absolutely insane!! Definately worth downloading for the space > other 1 alone.  Healy alters the sounds on Bobby's mike, as he did often in the late 80's for the other 1.
 The first set is pretty average, though the Picasso Moon is probably the WORST one ever done.
Please, check out the other 1.  You'll be glad you did.

grate show!!!!!!!! fine show with a great iko kick ass bertha cool victim spacey he's gone and phat other one.space is all melty and liquidy. really cool pre middi space.

downloading this show is NOT a bad idea.

Foolish Heart! I have been looking for a killer version of Foolish Heart for a while.  A friend recommended this version - and a great version it is! A great show - especially The Other One as previously noted by others.  And great sound quality on this as well.

the bus came by, and I got on, that's when it all began! This always was one of my favorite tapes. I think I've had about a dozen copies of this second set, and could never hold on to them. They always mysteriously grew legs, and walked off....Oh well, happy to share the love. Every so often you could just feel the magic flowing from the band. The magic was on this night!

Terrific show. Really enjoyable show, the boys are in good form and obviously engaged. Interesting song selection and great energy from everyone, especially Jerry, Phil and the drummers.  Also I love the sound of this board, everythings nice and balanced.  Really worth a listen especially if your a big 89/90 fan like myself.
crawling interesting. not perfect, but it sprouts legs and crawls along a foggy, steamy terrain. fairly solid throughout and some wild melty vibes to it.
Great Other One 5 stars for sound quality and the amazing other one (including space)
wow This foolish heart is awesome.  Makes me wanna dance
Foolish Heart Indeed a subjective call but I think the best Foolish Heart is from Oxford Maine 7/2/88.  Worth checking it out for the Foolish Heart fan.
music i was at this show. wow. best other one ever. billys b day . fun
